  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. Add sesame oil and sauté garlic and ginger until fragrant (about 1 minute).",
    "Add chicken pieces to the pan and cook for about 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown and cooked through.",
    "Remove chicken from the pan and set aside. In the same pan, add sauerkraut, green onions, soy sauce, fish sauce, rice vinegar, salt, and a pinch of pepper.",
    "Stir-fry for about 3 minutes until sauerkraut is tender but still slightly crisp, adding chicken back into the mixture if you like it extra flavorful.",
    "Serve hot with steamed basmati rice or noodles."
  ],
